ification tasks such as authorship identification, text categorization, genre classification, sentiment analysis etc. Furthermore character linguistic sequences are the basis for linguistic modeling and subsequent applications such as speech recognition, language identification etc. In addition to the above language technology oriented research, the present volume aims to give insight to the theoretical value of linguistic sequences. Sequences in texts can be produced by a number of different factors, either external to the linguistic system or by its own grammatical structure. This volume hosts contributions which will analyze linguistic sequences using quantitative methods under the synergetic theoretical framework that can explain their role in the linguistic system.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aComputational linguisticsxResearch. 4aQuantitative Linguistics, Sequence Analysis, Mathematical Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aMacutek, Ján, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMikros, George K., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103947710 cprintz978311036273240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036287940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110362879423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110362879.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHAL